Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo Osun State Chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party has asked the Federal High Court sitting in Osogbo to invalidate the appointment of Mr Amitolu Shittu as the Director-General of Amotekun Corps in the state. The PDP, in an originating summons dated May 7, 2020 filed on behalf of the party and its chairman, Sunday Atidade, by their counsel, Mr Taofiq Tewogbade, also asked for an order of the court, perpetually retraining Osun State House of Assembly and all security agencies in the state from recognising or dealing with Shittu in his capacity as DG, Amotekun. Others joined in the suit, apart from Governor Adegboyega Oyetola and Osun State House of Assembly, are the Nigeria Police Force, the Nigerian Army, Nigerian Navy, Nigerian Air Force, Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, Nigeria Customs Service  and Nigeria Immigration Service. Copyright PUNCH.
